The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Shastri: Dhoni, Warne the best captains
                                                                                                                                                                                           Shastri: Dhoni, Warne the best captains
            LOKENDRA PRATAP SAHI                      
	Calcutta: Ravi Shastri, who had the potential to emerge as Indias finest captain (he did lead briefly, though, in the late 1980s), has picked Mahendra Singh Dhoni and Shane Warne as the best captains in the ongoing Indian Premier League.         
	In a chat with The Telegraph on Tuesday, Shastri said: Dhoni has been handling pressure extremely well and has the ability to come up with the unexpected As for Warne, full marks to him for motivating a somewhat young team Also, he has been leading from the front.         
	While Dhoni is captaining the Chennai Super Kings, Warne is at the helm of the Rajasthan Royals.                                                                                                                          
